\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8247em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4519em;margin-left:-0.0785em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2481em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8247em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4519em;margin-left:-0.0785em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2481em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">]</span></span></span></span></span></span>","key":"nYj2jZoRiH"}],"key":"mSbuAeueMK"}],"key":"lmUVRwj0wH"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"Phi = X\nN, M = Phi.shape\n\n\ndef sigmoid(z):\n    return jnp.exp(z) / (1 + jnp.exp(z))\n\n\ndef log_sigmoid(z):\n    return z - jnp.log(1 + jnp.exp(z))\n\n\ndef logdensity_fn(w, alpha=1.0):\n    \"\"\"The log-probability density function of the posterior distribution of the model.\"\"\"\n    log_an = log_sigmoid(Phi @ w)\n    an = Phi @ w\n    log_likelihood_term = y * log_an + (1 - y) * jnp.log(1 - sigmoid(an))\n    prior_term = alpha * w @ w / 2\n\n    return -prior_term + log_likelihood_term.sum()","key":"xmLjtItHd3"},{"type":"outputs","id":"cF-AiHr7KvKhWixwPi8ri","children":[],"key":"wcPuzSBbr9"}],"key":"UMt7QPNYif"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":111,"column":1},"end":{"line":111,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pathfinder: Parallel Quasi-Newton Variational Inference","position":{"start":{"line":111,"column":1},"end":{"line":111,"column":1}},"key":"FGofLS4iiQ"}],"identifier":"pathfinder-parallel-quasi-newton-variational-inference","label":"Pathfinder: Parallel Quasi-Newton Variational Inference","html_id":"pathfinder-parallel-quasi-newton-variational-inference","implicit":true,"key":"Hux4RCMqyA"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Starting from a random initialization, Pathfinder locates normal approximations to the target\ndensity along a quasi-Newton optimization path, with local covariance estimated using the inverse Hessian\nestimates produced by the optimizer. Pathfinder returns draws from the approximation with the lowest\nestimated Kullback-Leibler (KL) divergence to the true posterior.\nThe optimizer is the limited memory BFGS algorithm.","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"inU8BVPQod"}],"key":"HoSCxDNHNx"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To help understand the approximations that pathfinder evaluates during its run, here we plot for each step of the L-BFGS optimizer the approximation of the posterior distribution of the model derived by pathfinder and its ELBO:","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"oz4CgrtQ8u"}],"key":"eRREWlfyEd"}],"key":"YkS9RXAFnM"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"# L-BFGS can occasionally fail to converge from a bad initialization;\n# retry until the ELBO path is finite.\nstop = 0\nwhile stop == 0:\n    rng_key, init_key, infer_key = jax.random.split(rng_key, 3)\n    w0 = jax.random.multivariate_normal(init_key, 2.0 + jnp.zeros(M), jnp.eye(M))\n    _, info = blackjax.vi.pathfinder.approximate(infer_key, logdensity_fn, w0, ftol=1e-6)\n    path = info.path\n    stop = np.isfinite(path.elbo).mean()","key":"baXLjhRFh6"},{"type":"outputs","id":"5PlPEctud54zu3ce8ID0J","children":[],"key":"dMueky7NSj"}],"key":"vxHXplZl7c"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"def ellipse_confidence(mu, cov, ax, c, n_std=2.0):\n    import numpy as np\n\n    lambda_, v = np.linalg.eig(cov)\n    lambda_ = np.sqrt(lambda_)\n    ellipse = Ellipse(\n        xy=(*mu,),\n        width=lambda_[0] * n_std * 2,\n        height=lambda_[1] * n_std * 2,\n        angle=np.degrees(np.arctan2(*v[:, 0][::-1])),\n        facecolor=c,\n        edgecolor=\"b\",\n        alpha=0.1,\n    )\n    return ax.add_artist(ellipse)\n\n\nstep = 0.1\nx_, y_ = jnp.mgrid[-1:3:step, -1:3:step]\npos_ = jnp.dstack((x_, y_))\nlogp_ = jnp.nan_to_num(\n    jax.vmap(logdensity_fn)(pos_.reshape(-1, M)).reshape(pos_.shape[0], pos_.shape[1]),\n    nan=-1e10,\n)\nlevels_ = jnp.percentile(logp_.flatten(), jnp.linspace(60, 100, 10))\n\n\nsteps = (jnp.isfinite(path.elbo)).sum()\nrows = int(jnp.ceil(steps / 3))\nfig, axs = plt.subplots(rows, 3, figsize=(15, 5 * rows), sharex=True, sharey=True)\n\nfor i, ax in zip(range(steps), axs.flatten()):\n\n    ax.contour(x_, y_, logp_, levels=levels_)\n    state = jax.tree.map(lambda x: x[i], path)\n    sample_state, _ = blackjax.vi.pathfinder.sample(rng_key, state, 10_000)\n    position_path = path.position[: i + 1]\n    ax.plot(\n        position_path[:, 0],\n        position_path[:, 1],\n        marker=\"*\",\n        linestyle=\"--\",\n        markersize=10,\n    )\n    mu_i, cov_i = sample_state.mean(0), jnp.cov(sample_state, rowvar=False)\n    ellipse_confidence(mu_i, cov_i, ax, \"r\")\n    ax.set_title(f\"Iteration: {i+1}\\nEstimated ELBO: {state.elbo:.2f}\")\nplt.show()","visibility":"hide","key":"QeTQkS0lbJ"},{"type":"outputs","id":"jOfYYxbgU9NmprmqPkPFX","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 1500x3000 with 18 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"},"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"400a4eb2b95063db38f54a7c234b741c","path":"/sampling-book/build/400a4eb2b95063db38f54a7c234b741c.png"}}},"key":"o2MuaHjLi0"}],"visibility":"show","key":"Mv0g3Yf1fk"}],"data":{"tags":[]},"visibility":"show","key":"gAsyp0xWF4"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":186,"column":1},"end":{"line":186,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pathfinder as a Variational Inference Method","position":{"start":{"line":186,"column":1},"end":{"line":186,"column":1}},"key":"oqoSlwIYac"}],"identifier":"pathfinder-as-a-variational-inference-method","label":"Pathfinder as a Variational Inference Method","html_id":"pathfinder-as-a-variational-inference-method","implicit":true,"key":"LEXd1KzB3A"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pathfinder can be used as a variational inference method. We first create a pathfinder object ","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"GuF1pEu3yZ"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"pf","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"pCaVtpKwEC"},{"type":"text","value":" which contains two functions ","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"CEh4jx1ktP"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"init","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"aH1soCJ1io"},{"type":"text","value":" and ","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"OfS0cJZ6l9"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"sample","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"EwJDFnxLIj"},{"type":"text","value":":","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"key":"IHOOILEnPz"}],"key":"zbD0JLSNXU"}],"key":"ccYqubqDwx"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"pf = blackjax.pathfinder(logdensity_fn)\nrng_key, approx_key = jax.random.split(rng_key)\nstate, _ = pf.init(approx_key, w0, ftol=1e-4)","key":"uyBXmJ1JoE"},{"type":"outputs","id":"45jTi1__ZyCaHXVDoq6en","children":[],"key":"RTKivpPbJG"}],"key":"GRSwAzddPN"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":196,"column":1},"end":{"line":196,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can now get samples from the approximation:","position":{"start":{"line":196,"column":1},"end":{"line":196,"column":1}},"key":"ZyLxFRNEz8"}],"key":"sSfRurY0VA"}],"key":"NZe4rTGEou"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"rng_key, sample_key = jax.random.split(rng_key)\nsamples, _ = pf.sample(sample_key, state, 5_000)","key":"hWlIgl4YoV"},{"type":"outputs","id":"-Q5TDggItmx8zSCrYtJ6s","children":[],"key":"tA5TL2Hxwg"}],"key":"yZB0bdnFcj"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":203,"column":1},"end":{"line":203,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And display the trace:","position":{"start":{"line":203,"column":1},"end":{"line":203,"column":1}},"key":"aPihKaZgB8"}],"key":"DeCzv2qZO6"}],"key":"HotSpnfMr4"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8, 2), sharey=True)\nfor i, axi in enumerate(ax):\n    axi.plot(samples[:, i])\n    axi.set_title(f\"$w_{i}$\")\nplt.show()","visibility":"hide","key":"ZIP6Hf9ZSq"},{"type":"outputs","id":"U6OkjHBIkUA8GpwVt1pqt","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 800x200 with 2 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"},"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"3495181114b6a59c3c437e234abf9bbe","path":"/sampling-book/build/3495181114b6a59c3c437e234abf9bbe.png"}}},"key":"IhmhIwrKKH"}],"visibility":"show","key":"mUJbDUgpIu"}],"data":{"tags":[]},"visibility":"show","key":"ufnqeeDVsW"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":215,"column":1},"end":{"line":215,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Please note that pathfinder is implemented as follows:","position":{"start":{"line":215,"column":1},"end":{"line":215,"column":1}},"key":"pWu7ovmJj6"}],"key":"mXKX9e0OYW"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":217,"column":1},"end":{"line":219,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":217,"column":1},"end":{"line":217,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"it runs L-BFGS optimization and finds the best approximation in the ","position":{"start":{"line":217,"column":1},"end":{"line":217,"column":1}},"key":"NmlHWZFVXm"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"init","position":{"start":{"line":217,"column":1},"end":{"line":217,"column":1}},"key":"nREZZYBrVa"},{"type":"text","value":" phase","position":{"start":{"line":217,"column":1},"end":{"line":217,"column":1}},"key":"lpNgy7LGpD"}],"key":"lbtjiSHOzW"}],"key":"NXeT2aSK96"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":218,"column":1},"end":{"line":219,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"inlineCode","value":"step","position":{"start":{"line":218,"column":1},"end":{"line":218,"column":1}},"key":"OZuVokcNFb"},{"type":"text","value":" phase it’s just sampling from a multinormal distribution, whose parameters have been already estimated","position":{"start":{"line":218,"column":1},"end":{"line":218,"column":1}},"key":"seZhiBQk4f"}],"key":"yziEpECdE1"}],"key":"r4d5kIQMlV"}],"key":"djIARNVslP"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hence it makes sense to ","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"JjGRGiiplG"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"jit","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"Y11fmm6II3"},{"type":"text","value":" the ","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"RU5sNzHYui"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"init","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"MEHCPQYeH0"},{"type":"text","value":" function and then use the ","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"XygoFcnMgv"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"sample","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"cm4tSDbmzU"},{"type":"text","value":" helper function in the pathfinder object instead of implementing the inference loop:","position":{"start":{"line":220,"column":1},"end":{"line":220,"column":1}},"key":"NeZWNJ1YOA"}],"key":"MfFcC6IkEK"}],"key":"nBp53YtXmm"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"%%time\n\nstate, _ = jax.jit(pf.init)(approx_key, w0)\nsamples, _ = pf.sample(sample_key, state, 5_000)","key":"ccNwIglVVL"},{"type":"outputs","id":"GWukSiUskTfddD4mr9VLg","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":"CPU times: user 6.02 s, sys: 98.3 ms, total: 6.12 s\nWall time: 3.24 s\n"},"key":"NONVMXcsE8"}],"key":"adefuOoKKi"}],"key":"oS9qAm7Bb3"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":229,"column":1},"end":{"line":229,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Quick comparison against the Rosenbluth-Metropolis-Hastings kernel ","position":{"start":{"line":229,"column":1},"end":{"line":229,"column":1}},"key":"OR8cUV6ZlI"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"rmh","position":{"start":{"line":229,"column":1},"end":{"line":229,"column":1}},"key":"vIxVjXzFMb"},{"type":"text","value":":","position":{"start":{"line":229,"column":1},"end":{"line":229,"column":1}},"key":"omWTECkJg0"}],"key":"Z3uZXSlV3t"}],"key":"s7eeIdbhKk"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"def inference_loop(rng_key, kernel, initial_state, num_samples):\n    @jax.jit\n    def one_step(state, rng_key):\n        state, info = kernel(rng_key, state)\n        return state, (state, info)\n\n    keys = jax.random.split(rng_key, num_samples)\n    return jax.lax.scan(one_step, initial_state, keys)\n\n\nrmh = blackjax.rmh(\n    logdensity_fn, blackjax.mcmc.random_walk.normal(sigma=jnp.ones(M) * 0.7)\n)\nstate_rmh = rmh.init(w0)\nrng_key, sample_key = jax.random.split(rng_key)\n_, (samples_rmh, _) = inference_loop(sample_key, rmh.step, state_rmh, 5_000)","key":"hPp7yHau4r"},{"type":"outputs","id":"Omyp289d9z4UO0lUjsKw5","children":[],"key":"bPU3v6dNSi"}],"key":"YkwgWxUmiA"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(10, 4), sharey=True)\nfor i in range(2):\n    ax[i, 0].plot(samples_rmh.position[:, i])\n    ax[i, 0].axvline(x=300, c=\"tab:red\")\n    ax[i, 0].set_ylabel(f\"$w_{i}$\")\n    ax[i, 1].plot(samples[:, i])\n\nax[0, 0].set_title(\"RMH\")\nax[0, 1].set_title(\"Pathfinder\")\nfig.show()","visibility":"hide","key":"bv1jBTRqma"},{"type":"outputs","id":"PsuVtuKa-9BVDtmvci2GZ","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 1000x400 with 4 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"},"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"1e19e3b418a02e1bc0bb411eb9c07e08","path":"/sampling-book/build/1e19e3b418a02e1bc0bb411eb9c07e08.png"}}},"key":"gpo69tFGmx"}],"visibility":"show","key":"diE5ztD9sb"}],"data":{"tags":[]},"visibility":"show","key":"rw9YDNt2br"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":265,"column":1},"end":{"line":265,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pathfinder as an Initialization Tool for MCMC Kernels","position":{"start":{"line":265,"column":1},"end":{"line":265,"column":1}},"key":"OLUiWwpRxa"}],"identifier":"pathfinder-as-an-initialization-tool-for-mcmc-kernels","label":"Pathfinder as an Initialization Tool for MCMC Kernels","html_id":"pathfinder-as-an-initialization-tool-for-mcmc-kernels","implicit":true,"key":"t9E4OSWcjS"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":267,"column":1},"end":{"line":267,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pathfinder uses internally the inverse hessian estimation of the L-BFGS optimizer to evaluate the approximations to the target distribution along the quasi-Newton optimization path.","position":{"start":{"line":267,"column":1},"end":{"line":267,"column":1}},"key":"rrzEoDgPIx"}],"key":"ELkp3iswPl"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":269,"column":1},"end":{"line":269,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can calculate explic